#. <section class="sutta" id="an6.32"><article><div class="hgroup"><p class="division">
msgctxt "an6.32:0.1"
msgid "Aṅguttara Nikāya 6"
msgstr "Numbered Discourses 6"

#. </p><p>
msgctxt "an6.32:0.2"
msgid "4. devatāvagga"
msgstr "4. Deities"

#. </p><h1>
msgctxt "an6.32:0.3"
msgid "32. Paṭhamaaparihānasutta"
msgstr "32. Non-decline (1st)"

#. </h1></div><p>
#. <a class="sc" id="sc1"></a>
msgctxt "an6.32:1.1"
msgid ""
"Atha kho aññatarā devatā abhikkantāya rattiyā abhikkantavaṇṇā kevalakappaṃ "
"jetavanaṃ obhāsetvā yena bhagavā tenupasaṅkami; upasaṅkamitvā bhagavantaṃ "
"abhivādetvā ekamantaṃ aṭṭhāsi. Ekamantaṃ ṭhitā kho sā devatā bhagavantaṃ "
"etadavoca:"
msgstr ""
"Then, late at night, a glorious deity, lighting up the entire Jeta’s Grove, "
"went up to the Buddha, bowed, stood to one side, and said to him:"

#. </p><p>
#. <a class="sc" id="sc2"></a>
msgctxt "an6.32:2.1"
msgid "“Chayime, bhante, dhammā bhikkhuno aparihānāya saṃvattanti."
msgstr "“Sir, these six things don’t lead to the decline of a mendicant."

msgctxt "an6.32:2.2"
msgid "Katame cha?"
msgstr "What six?"

#. VAR: paṭisanthāragāravatā → paṭisandhāragāravatā (mr)
msgctxt "an6.32:2.3"
msgid ""
"Satthugāravatā, dhammagāravatā, saṃghagāravatā, sikkhāgāravatā, "
"appamādagāravatā, paṭisanthāragāravatā—"
msgstr ""
"Respect for the Teacher, for the teaching, for the Saṅgha, for the training, "
"for diligence, and for hospitality."

msgctxt "an6.32:2.4"
msgid "ime kho, bhante, cha dhammā bhikkhuno aparihānāya saṃvattantī”ti."
msgstr "These six things don’t lead to the decline of a mendicant.”"

msgctxt "an6.32:2.5"
msgid "Idamavoca sā devatā."
msgstr "That’s what that deity said,"

msgctxt "an6.32:2.6"
msgid "Samanuñño satthā ahosi."
msgstr "and the teacher approved."

msgctxt "an6.32:2.7"
msgid ""
"Atha kho sā devatā “samanuñño me satthā”ti bhagavantaṃ abhivādetvā "
"padakkhiṇaṃ katvā tatthevantaradhāyi."
msgstr ""
"Then that deity, knowing that the teacher approved, bowed, and respectfully "
"circled the Buddha, keeping him on his right, before vanishing right there."

#. </p><p>
#. <a class="pts-vp-pli" id="pts-vp-pli3.331"></a>
#. <a class="sc" id="sc3"></a>
msgctxt "an6.32:3.1"
msgid "Atha kho bhagavā tassā rattiyā accayena bhikkhū āmantesi:"
msgstr ""
"Then, when the night had passed, the Buddha told the mendicants all that had "
"happened, adding:"

msgctxt "an6.32:3.2"
msgid ""
"“imaṃ, bhikkhave, rattiṃ aññatarā devatā abhikkantāya rattiyā "
"abhikkantavaṇṇā kevalakappaṃ jetavanaṃ obhāsetvā yenāhaṃ tenupasaṅkami; "
"upasaṅkamitvā maṃ abhivādetvā ekamantaṃ aṭṭhāsi. Ekamantaṃ ṭhitā kho, "
"bhikkhave, sā devatā maṃ etadavoca:"
msgstr ""

msgctxt "an6.32:3.3"
msgid "‘chayime, bhante, dhammā bhikkhuno aparihānāya saṃvattanti."
msgstr ""

msgctxt "an6.32:3.4"
msgid "Katame cha?"
msgstr ""

msgctxt "an6.32:3.5"
msgid ""
"Satthugāravatā, dhammagāravatā, saṅghagāravatā, sikkhāgāravatā, "
"appamādagāravatā, paṭisanthāragāravatā—"
msgstr ""

msgctxt "an6.32:3.6"
msgid "ime kho, bhante, cha dhammā bhikkhuno aparihānāya saṃvattantī’ti."
msgstr ""

msgctxt "an6.32:3.7"
msgid "Idamavoca, bhikkhave, sā devatā."
msgstr ""

msgctxt "an6.32:3.8"
msgid "Idaṃ vatvā maṃ abhivādetvā padakkhiṇaṃ katvā tatthevantaradhāyīti."
msgstr ""

#. </p><blockquote class="gatha"><p>
#. <a class="sc" id="sc4"></a>
msgctxt "an6.32:4.1"
msgid "Satthugaru dhammagaru,"
msgstr "“Respect for the Teacher and the teaching,"

#. <br>
msgctxt "an6.32:4.2"
msgid "saṅghe ca tibbagāravo;"
msgstr "and keen respect for the Saṅgha;"

#. <br>
msgctxt "an6.32:4.3"
msgid "Appamādagaru bhikkhu,"
msgstr "a mendicant who respects diligence"

#. <br>
msgctxt "an6.32:4.4"
msgid "paṭisanthāragāravo;"
msgstr "and hospitality"

#. <br>
msgctxt "an6.32:4.5"
msgid "Abhabbo parihānāya,"
msgstr "can’t decline,"

#. <br>
msgctxt "an6.32:4.6"
msgid "nibbānasseva santike”ti."
msgstr "and has drawn near to extinguishment.”"

#. </p></blockquote><p class="endsection">
msgctxt "an6.32:4.7"
msgid "Dutiyaṃ."
msgstr ""
